It looks like **[DTL Nobel Condensed](http://web.archive.org/web/20131219103432/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=URW&ffam=DTLNobelT%20Condensed%20-%20Regular&fid=36625b9af5a0f7d7daa586ce4c256314&fsize=60&text=EASTERN%20COLUMBIA%20BUILDING&wrap=2)** an old Dutch Type Library font which should be normally acquired by URW++ (but I can't find it in URW++ collection)  
A close similar is **[Nobel Condensed](http://web.archive.org/web/20131219103432/http:/www.findmyfont.com/index.php/fonts/font-preview?fset=Font-Bureau&ffam=Nobel%20Condensed%20-%20Regular&fid=616c807cb2758dec44517aded1cf8c99&fsize=60&text=EASTERN%20COLUMBIA%20BUILDING&wrap=2)** by Font Bureau
